.TH SINGINE 1 "2026-03-16" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine \- top-level command index for the Singine platform
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine
[\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B singine
is the top-level entry point for the Singine platform. This page is an index of
top-level commands only. Each command has its own dedicated manpage for details,
subcommands, options, and examples.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B context
Inspect terminal context and sourced environment.
.TP
.B bridge
SQLite and JDBC bridge operations.
Merges local Singine, AI session, Silkpage, and Collibra data into a single
queryable store.
See
.BR singine-bridge (1).
.TP
.B jdbc-url
Print the JDBC URL for the bridge database.
.TP
.B xml
Generate XML request, response, and heatmap artifacts.
.TP
.B man
Open a Singine manpage by topic.
See
.BR singine-man (1).
.TP
.B install
Install the launcher and bundled manpages.
.TP
.B runtime
Inspect runtime capabilities and execute wrapped commands.
See
.BR singine-runtime (1).
.TP
.B auth
Authentication bootstrap and TOTP login commands.
.TP
.B idp
Identity provider operations.
.TP
.B decide
Send a governance decision request.
Falls back to a local JSON record when the Singine server is not running.
See
.BR singine-decide (1).
.TP
.B model
Inspect Singine model objects and bridge surfaces.
.TP
.B policy
Manage governed policy packs and policy-backed execution workflows.
Covers Claude, Codex, and OpenAI-API systems.
See
.BR singine-policy (1).
.TP
.B ai
Governed AI session recording, permission tracking, and session-data
centralisation for Claude, Codex, and OpenAI.
Every conversation is stored as a named session with a manifest, ordered
interactions, and mandates granted during the session.
Sessions can be listed, inspected, and synced into a local SQLite
bridge for JDBC and downstream Singine access.
See
.BR singine-ai (1).
.TP
.B activity
Inspect, instantiate, and evaluate activity taxonomy entries.
.TP
.B singe
Render governed identities from @mentions.
.TP
.B find
Find filesystem paths related to a topic via the
.I filesAboutTopic
activity.
.TP
.B mv
Move filesystem paths from stdin into a destination directory via the
.I fileListTo
activity.
.TP
.B transfer
File transfer and queue/stack helpers.
.TP
.B smtp
SMTP test and send helpers.
.SH AI CONVERSATION DATA
Singine records every AI conversation — regardless of provider — as a governed
session. The following command sequence covers the full journey from listing
sessions to centralising the data behind each conversation.
.SS 1. Start a governed provider session
.nf
singine ai claude --model claude-sonnet-4-6
singine ai codex --model gpt-5-codex
singine ai openai --model gpt-4o
.fi
.PP
Each session records a session id, provider, model, timestamps, a session URN,
a provider object reference for later API mapping, ordered interactions, and
mandates granted during the session.
.SS 2. List all recorded sessions
.nf
singine ai session list
.fi
.PP
Shows all recorded runtime sessions under
.IR ~/.singine/ai/sessions/ .
.SS 3. Inspect one session
.nf
singine ai session show SESSION-ID
.fi
.PP
Prints the full session bundle:
.IP \(bu 2
manifest
.IP \(bu 2
interactions
.IP \(bu 2
mandates
.SS 4. Check provider configuration
.nf
singine ai status
singine ai status --json
.fi
.PP
Reports configured AI providers.
.SS 5. Centralise sessions into SQLite
.nf
# Sync the most recent session into a named bridge database
singine ai last session data --db /tmp/singine-ai.db

# Or open an interactive session that auto-syncs on close
singine ai claude --model claude-sonnet-4-6 --db /tmp/singine-ai.db
.fi
.SS 6. Query centralised data via the bridge
.nf
singine bridge sources --db /tmp/singine-ai.db
singine bridge search --db /tmp/singine-ai.db "SESSION-TOPIC"
singine jdbc-url --db /tmp/singine-ai.db
.fi
.SS 7. Review governance decisions for a session
.nf
singine policy ai report --ai-system claude
singine policy ai report --ai-system codex
.fi
.SH POLICY SYNC
Singine's AI policy workflow is available through the top-level
.B singine policy ai
command family.
The canonical flow is:
.IP "1."
sync a canonical policy pack from LDAP or LDIF sources into a dedicated policy
repository with
.BR "singine policy ai sync" ;
.IP "2."
evaluate Claude or OpenAI/Codex requests against that synced pack with
.BR "singine policy ai evaluate" ;
.IP "3."
persist approvals for governed Collibra paths, repos, or lambda names when a
change is sanctioned with
.BR "singine policy ai approve" .
